The White House Press Secretary, Robert Gibbs, provided a briefing on August 7, 2009. He discussed the President's upcoming schedule, including travel plans and events. He also addressed questions on the economy, healthcare reform, and town hall meetings. Additionally, he mentioned the agreement between the White House and PhRMA (Pharmaceutical Research and Manufacturers of America) on healthcare savings, and the President's upcoming meeting with Justice Sonia Sotomayor.